# PVL UI — Visual rules

You are working on Peptide Visual Lab. Read these conventions before writing or modifying any visual code. Violating them produces design drift that T1 will reject.

## Design language
- **Light-first** by default. Dark mode must also render correctly. Test both.
- **Stripe-level calm**: ample whitespace, subdued saturation, motion only when it serves a state change. No bouncing, no rainbow gradients, no oversaturated CTAs.
- **Professional, not playful**. PVL is a scientific instrument. No emojis in production UI copy unless Said explicitly requests them.
- **Mobile responsive at 375px width** is mandatory (`feedback_mobile_responsive.md`). Use `px-4 sm:px-6`, `grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-N`, `flex-wrap`.

## Theme tokens (NEVER hardcode colors)
- `bg-card`, `bg-background`, `bg-muted/30`
- `text-foreground`, `text-muted-foreground`
- `border-border`, `border-border/40`, `border-border/60`
- Classification palette tokens (defined in `ui/src/index.css`):
  - `--helix` (helix-positive peptides)
  - `--ssw` (SSW-positive peptides)
  - `--ff-helix` (fibril-forming helix candidates)
  - `--ff-ssw` (fibril-forming SSW candidates)
- Tailwind utility classes use these tokens — never write `#3b82f6` or `bg-blue-500`.

## Component primitives
- Use shadcn/ui: `Card`, `Button`, `Badge`, `Tabs`, `Tooltip`, `HoverCard`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `Collapsible`, `DropdownMenu`.
- Icons: `lucide-react`. Standard size `w-4 h-4` for body, `w-3.5 h-3.5` for inline, `w-5 h-5` for hero.
- Animations: `framer-motion` only. Calm easing (`easeInOut` or `easeOut`), 200-400ms durations. No spring bounce unless explicit.
- Charts: `recharts` for standard charts (BarChart, ScatterChart, etc.). Raw SVG for custom (HelicalWheel, PositionBars).

## Component pattern
```typescript
interface MyComponentProps {
  peptides: Peptide[];
  className?: string;
}

export function MyComponent({ peptides, className }: MyComponentProps) {
  // hooks at top, then derived state, then handlers, then JSX
}
```
- Named export, not default (except pages — those use default).
- Props as explicit interface; never `Record<string, any>`.
- No `any` types — use `Peptide` from `@/types/peptide` and other canonical types.

## State
- `Zustand` for global state: `datasetStore`, `thresholdStore`, `chartSelectionStore`, `demoStore`.
- `useState` for local UI only. No new state libraries.
- Use `??` not `||` for numeric fallbacks (`0` is a valid value).

## Layout discipline
- Page header pattern: subtitle + title + meta row. See `Results.tsx` and `PeptideDetail.tsx` for canonical layout.
- KPI cards in a responsive grid `grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-4 gap-3` or `gap-4`.
- Drill-down inspector via `useDrillDown` from `@/components/drilldown/DrillDownProvider`. Never duplicate the Sheet pattern.
- BgDotGrid for hero backgrounds; never add another background pattern.

## Pre-flight before creating a new component
1. Search for existing: `grep -rn "<concept-keyword>" ui/src/components/ ui/src/pages/`
2. Read any matches in full.
3. Decide explicitly per match: extend / refactor / replace / leave alone. Justify in one sentence.
4. Default = extend or refactor existing. Only create new if no existing component fits.

## What NOT to do
- Don't add CSS modules or styled-components. Tailwind only.
- Don't add npm dependencies without flagging T1.
- Don't write tests that test implementation details — test behavior.
- Don't add unmotivated abstractions. The boring obvious version is preferred.
- Don't generate emoji-heavy copy. Stripe-level means quiet.

## Tests
- Vitest + jsdom + `@testing-library/react`.
- Test files in `__tests__/` siblings: `MyComponent.tsx` → `__tests__/MyComponent.test.tsx`.
- Use factory functions for test data, not inline literals everywhere.

